data.title: NBA at 75: 2000s saw MJ-LBJ shift, 'Malice at the Palace'
data.meta_description: As Michael Jordan gave way to LeBron James, and as traditional forms of communication began to yield to the birth and growth of new media, the 2000s were all about making transitions — on the court and off — for the NBA and its fans.
